episodes.title: Old School Training
episodes.description: Jake is the Magical Protector of the NYC. Torn between fun and duties.

episodes.title: The Talented Mr. Long
episodes.description: The talent show and its unique prize.

episodes.title: The Legend of the Dragon Tooth
episodes.description: Jake's little sister is about to lose her first tooth. But since it's a dragon tooth, it has mystical powers. The Tooth Fairy's assistant, Dr. Diente, has been biding his time until a dragon tooth came along. Seizing his opportunity, Diente grabs the Tooth Fairy's wand and goes after Haley. But he didn't figure on a mystical shield guarding the Long house, as well as the American Dragon.

episodes.title: Act 4, Scene 15
episodes.description: Jake tries out for a part in "Antony and Cleopatra" in order to get close to the girl of his dreams.

episodes.title: Adventures in Troll-Sitting
episodes.description: How to keep a one-eyed Troll out of the sun?

episodes.title: Fu Dog Takes a Walk
episodes.description: While Jake learns to focus, Fu is alone and an allergic dame dog-naps the rare Shar-Pei on the way to a ball game.

episodes.title: Professor Rotwood's Thesis
episodes.description: Professor Rotwood offers his students $500 for physical proof of the existence of magical creatures.

disney_plus.title: The Egg
disney_plus.description: HuntsGirl succeeds at stealing a magical Griffin egg. How will the American Dragon return it to its grieving mother before it hatches?

disney_plus.title: The Heist
disney_plus.description: A Dark Wizard steals Leprechaun gold. Jake and Fu have a sophisticated plan to stay a few steps ahead of the opponent, but they cannot know what unexpected surprises await them.

disney_plus.title: Dragon Summit
disney_plus.description: Jake is tested by the World Dragon Council.

disney_plus.title: Body Guard Duty
disney_plus.description: Jake must protect The Oracle Twins from trolls.

disney_plus.title: Shapeshifter
disney_plus.description: Jake must pose as a troll in order to retrieve an orb from the huntsclan undetected. Trouble ensues when he misuses the shape shifting potion Fu Dog made for him and is captured by the Huntsmaster. Will Gramps find them before the potion wears off, revealing Jake's human form?

disney_plus.title: Ski Trip
disney_plus.description: Jake and his class go on an overnight ski trip.

disney_plus.title: The Long Weekend
disney_plus.description: Mr. Long takes Jake and his friends camping in New Jersey.

disney_plus.title: Eye of the Beholder
disney_plus.description: The Comedy: Fu Dog is forced to go undercover as a contestant in the "Miss Magical World." beauty pageant./ The Action: Grandpa, Fu Dog, and Jake race to stop Eli Pandarus from kidnapping "Miss Magical World," the missing piece in his diabolical plan to become the most powerful dark wizard.

disney_plus.title: Jake Takes the Cake
disney_plus.description: Gremlins threaten to ruin the wedding of two soap opera stars that Jake's mother has been hired to cater.

disney_plus.title: Hong Kong Knights
disney_plus.description: Facing the Dark Dragon. When Gramps met Fu. Can non-magical creatures fly? Can both Oracle twins be happy?

disney_plus.title: The Halloween Bash
disney_plus.description: Jake throws a Halloween party for both magical and non-magical creatures.

disney_plus.title: Fu and Tell
disney_plus.description: Haley's classmate brings her adorable pet to school. Fu faces this magical cat in battle, yet again. "Me-OW".

disney_plus.title: Flight of the Unicorn
disney_plus.description: A unicorn leaves her herd and ends up as a carnival display. Unicorns cannot live for long when separated from their herd! How will they reunite the unicorn with her family in time?

disney_plus.title: Keeping Shop
disney_plus.description: Jake and Gramps head to a Dragon Retreat, leaving Fu Dog, Trixie and Spud in charge of the electronics store. When mountain trolls start terrorising the area, it's up to them to put a stop it.

disney_plus.title: Ring Around the Dragon
disney_plus.description: Jake must save a runaway giant child from an unscrupulous wrestling promoter.

disney_plus.title: The Hunted
disney_plus.description: Still mournful over finding out Rose is the Huntsgirl, and thus being forced to shun her affections, Jake is kidnapped by The Huntsclan along with other magical creatures as part of their "Grand Equinox Hunt," where they are set free to be hunted down by the Huntsclan. When he doesn't drop subtle hints at Rose about the true nature of their relationship, he realizes that as a dragon, he must help a water-fearing mermaid, a hot-blooded brownie, a giantess, and an unlucky Leprechaun to defend themselves in the hunt.

disney_plus.title: Bring It On
disney_plus.description: Three sisters who once controlled the world are released from stone and wish to rule again. They can hypnotize and even trap magical creatures in stone. Who can stop them?

disney_plus.title: Half Baked
disney_plus.description: Jake must bake cupcakes for extra credit in his Home Eq class, but he accidentally includes a magical venom in the recipe.

disney_plus.title: The Academy
disney_plus.description: Spud breaks the HuntsClan encryption code and two trainees are captured. Jake and Spud replace them and go to the training facility to try to uncover another evil plot. What if Jake is caught? And who are the girls in Kara's vision who are fighting over Spud?

disney_plus.title: The Doppleganger Gang
disney_plus.description: Jake is overwhelmed by his responsibilities as the American Dragon, so he decides to use his powers to create identical copies of himself to help ease the workload. But one of the clones doesn't seem to be like the others.

disney_plus.title: Something Fishy This Way Comes
disney_plus.description: Jake's principal is not what she appears to be.

disney_plus.title: Breakout
disney_plus.description: Rose worries that her and Jake are spending too much time together and the Huntsmaster is growing suspicious of her allegiance. Meanwhile Jake is going through this first ten-yearly dragon skin molting.

disney_plus.title: Family Business
disney_plus.description: Hayley steals the spotlight from Jake as she begins her dragon training with Master Sun Park. Meanwhile Fu gets a visit from an old friend.

disney_plus.title: Hero of the Hourglass
disney_plus.description: After successfully keeping a time traveling amulet out of the clutches of the Huntsclan, and getting grounded by his father in the process, Jake decided to use the amulet to go back to 1986 in order to reveal the existence of Dragons and other magical creatures to him. The trouble is, the shock of this revelation ends up breaking his parents up before he was even born, and now he has no other choice but to find a way to get them back together again.

disney_plus.title: Dreamscape
disney_plus.description: With the help of a dream charm from Rose, Jake tries to enter the subconscious of Rotwood in order to pass his mysterious test. During this effort, he accidentally release a Chimera from Rotwood's dream into everybody else's, and has to summon Spud and Trixie to defeat it. In the process of doing so, Jake finds out about his friends and foes, Trixie find out something about herself, and Rose discovers something new about her past, that may further diminish her loyalty to the Huntsclan.

disney_plus.title: A Befuddled Mind
disney_plus.description: Spud ends up in genius school.

disney_plus.title: Fool's Gold
disney_plus.description: In gratitude for rescuing them from some trolls, two leprechauns offer Jake a part-time job as security duty at a pawn shop they own, and the greed goes to his head as well as the heads of his friends... that is until the shop makes a deal with the huntsclan that could doom the entire magical wold.

disney_plus.title: Feeding Frenzy
disney_plus.description: Jake must protect the trident while competing with his cousin.

disney_plus.title: Haley Gone Wild
disney_plus.description: When dad says don't watch a TV show.

disney_plus.title: Supernatural Tuesday
disney_plus.description: When Nigel, the new British exchange student, keeps showing up Jake at school, Jake decides to run for class president and uses an ancient magical glove to read the minds of the voters. But when Jake discovers that Nigel is a magical wizard, they put their difference aside and join forces to defeat the monster who has returned to claim the coveted glove. Grandpa and Fu Dog give the shop a makeover when a new electronics shop, "Boomgarden's," opens up across the street.

disney_plus.title: The Rotwood Files
disney_plus.description: Jake plays a trick on Principal Rotwood, making him leave, only to have an even tougher principal take his place.

disney_plus.title: Hairy Christmas
disney_plus.description: Desperate to get out of his family's lame Christmas rituals, Jake uses his dragon duties to try to find a baby sasquatch and return him to his tribe before they go on a rampage throughout New York City. The only people who make this job harder than it already is are Professor Rotwood, and two flunkies from the Huntsclan.

disney_plus.title: Switcheroo
disney_plus.description: Jake and Haley are forced to re-examine their sibling rivalry when an enchanted mirror switches their bodies for a day and each must comically experience life as the other.

disney_plus.title: The Love Cruise
disney_plus.description: While Jake guards Cupid's arrows, he obsesses over Rose and decides to use the arrows on his school's Love Cruise dance.

disney_plus.title: Year of the Jake
disney_plus.description: When Jake is asked to watch over his Grandpa's shop, he accidentally curses it. Can he eliminate the curse before his Grandpa returns?

disney_plus.title: Homecoming
disney_plus.description: Jake and Rose come to a crossroads, as the Huntsclan achieve the power to eliminate all magical creatures.

disney_plus.title: Young at Heart
disney_plus.description: After Jake, Trixie, Spud, and Grandpa battle a magical creature, they discover their contact with the beast has left them drained of their youth. Jake is thrilled because he's now 21 years old and living it up, but Trixie and Spud end up in a retirement home. Jake realizes he'll grow up soon enough and must defeat the beast to restore their youth. An elderly Trixie and Spud try to adjust to life in a magical retirement home.

disney_plus.title: Siren Says
disney_plus.description: Jake is being auctioned off for a school bachelor fundraiser, but when he notices that the two contenders are a pretty girl, and a plain looking girl, to Trixie's dismay he manipulates the bidding so the pretty girl wins. But when Gramps fears that this pretty girl is actually a siren bent on his destruction, he and Trixie, Spud, and Fu try to convince Jake he made a bad choice. Trixie accidentally bids on Spud, and must spend a week with him as her "bachelor."

disney_plus.title: Shaggy Frog
disney_plus.description: When Spud is bitten by a magical frog and begins to develop cool "froggy" powers, against Jakes advice, he decides to ham it up in front of all the other students and finally enjoy all the perks of being part magical like his best friend. That is, until Huntsclan #88 and #89 come magical frog huntin'.

disney_plus.title: Nobody's Fu
disney_plus.description: Jake's loyalty to Fu Dog comes into question when he's assigned a new animal guardian-a totally cool hip-hop helper monkey named Bananas B. But when the evil Dragon Councilor Chang shows up and Bananas B changes sides, Jake realizes loyalty is hard to come by and apologizes to Fu for turning his back on his guardian. Spud feels betrayed after Trixie admits to burying an ugly sweater he gave her for her birthday.

disney_plus.title: Magic Enemy #1
disney_plus.description: When Rotwood sets Jake up for humiliation at school in an effort to put Jake off balance so he'll hopefully reveal his true dragon self, Jake starts venting on an online blog and unintentionally turns Rotwood into the magical world's public enemy #1. Once Jake discovers that there's a bounty on Rotwood's head, he realizes that he's said too much and has to convince the magical community to give up their quest and return things back to normal - even if Rotwood is still going to give Jake a hard time.

disney_plus.title: A Ghost Story
disney_plus.description: Jake, Spud, and Trixie are hoping for a little rest and relaxation and sign up to be camp counselors at Haley's summer camp. But when a legendary ghost story comes to life, Jake must put his vacation on hold and help all the junior campers face their fears to defeat the "ghosts" that are trying to steal their souls. Haley competes with a fellow camper for the coveted camp trophy.

disney_plus.title: Bite Father, Bite Son
disney_plus.description: The type of Vampire that feeds on Dragon blood is in NYC. They want the American Dragon. Jake has a secret weapon but so do they! How can he defeat them at night and when he is too weak to blow fire?

disney_plus.title: Game On
disney_plus.description: When Jake discovers a magical "game controller" device that he can use for his own life, he starts altering certain recent events in order to change the outcomes in his favor. When Jake can't keep up with the affects of all of his changes, he realizes it's better not to take shortcuts and just play the cards that life has dealt. Fu Dog is miserable when his vet puts him on a diet.

disney_plus.title: Furious Jealousy
disney_plus.description: Spud is after Stacey the cheerleader again, but his love can lead to great dangers.

disney_plus.title: Being Human
disney_plus.description: Jake takes a break from being the American Dragon and lets Haley take over, but an old enemy returns.

disney_plus.title: The Hong Kong Longs
disney_plus.description: Jake Long's family tours Hong Kong, actually for a special meeting of Dragons. Grandpa is abducted. In an effort to rescue him, Jake and his close friends use their extreme-sport skills but enter a trap. With grandpa hostage and the Dark Dragon so powerful, who can avert the capture of the entire Magical world?
